repo.description: The most widely used Python to C compiler
repo.name: cython

commit.message: Add a dedicated import hook for "cython.cimports.*" imports to make them fallback to unprefixed Python modules in plain Python code.
Fix the path based import in cimport meta hook to really do a complete import cycle rather than a simpler path search.
Make the Python-cimports test not depend on Cython being compiled but stand-alone runnable.

Use inline annotations instead of @cython.locals() decorators for compiled Cython source modules.
While at it, replace the "dict as set" usages in the Plex state transition implementation with real Python sets.
Move most of Parsing.pxd into Python annotations in Parsing.py.
Do not use "tuple[...]" due to old Python versions.
Fix and optimise some type annotations.
Fix a test after declaring the Scanner.position() method "cdef".
Improve some declarations in the Scanner class.

Make the "CythonCImports" fake package implementation in Shadow.py more robust by using importlib, by passing a partial package name (if used), and by setting module attributes along the fake package hierarchy.

title: Cleanup: use annotations instead of type overrides in pxd files
